1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:03,972
We're kind of a special pair, aren't we?

2
00:00:03,972 --> 00:00:06,472
Is it Eisei Ureshino?

3
00:00:06,472 --> 00:00:08,500
You're friends-with-benefits!

4
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:13,310
If you're free,
maybe we could get dinner together.

5
00:00:13,310 --> 00:00:17,650
If I could fall for someone
like Kusaka-kun, I'm sure...

6
00:00:17,650 --> 00:00:22,785
I could be happy.

7
00:00:22,785 --> 00:00:25,990
Instead of someone like Eisei Ureshino.

8
00:00:25,990 --> 00:00:28,910
Instead of a man like him.

9
00:00:29,605 --> 00:00:31,890
But I don't have plans tonight,

10
00:00:31,890 --> 00:00:35,360
so if you want, how about a meal?

11
00:00:35,360 --> 00:00:36,605
That's great.

12
00:00:36,605 --> 00:00:38,240
I can clock out soon.

13
00:00:38,240 --> 00:00:40,985
Wait for me downstairs.

14
00:00:40,985 --> 00:00:43,740
Oh, it's a promise.

15
00:00:43,740 --> 00:00:45,740
I'll be right there.

16
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:07,180
How about... a date tonight?

17
00:01:10,415 --> 00:01:12,320
What? Out of the blue?

18
00:01:12,320 --> 00:01:14,280
It's not out of the blue, isn't it?

19
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:16,421
We're special, after all.

20
00:01:16,421 --> 00:01:19,751
I seriously can't believe you.

21
00:01:19,751 --> 00:01:23,120
You were eavesdropping earlier,
weren't you?

22
00:01:25,652 --> 00:01:28,910
You have a really
nasty personality, you know.

23
00:01:28,910 --> 00:01:31,450
- I can't join you.
- Huh? Why not?

24
00:01:31,450 --> 00:01:34,330
Because I have plans with Kusaka-kun.

25
00:01:34,330 --> 00:01:35,705
Dinner, right?

26
00:01:35,705 --> 00:01:39,260
- I knew it.
- Then, let's meet after.

27
00:01:39,260 --> 00:01:40,760
What?

28
00:01:45,050 --> 00:01:47,510
I'll be at your place, Miporin.

29
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:55,300
What are you talking about?

30
00:01:56,420 --> 00:01:58,250
It's a promise.

31
00:02:14,795 --> 00:02:17,000
Sorry to have kept you waiting.

32
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,700
It's fine. Good work today.

33
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:20,074
You too.

34
00:02:20,074 --> 00:02:22,809
- Should we go then?
- Yeah.

35
00:02:25,233 --> 00:02:27,633
This is going to be a lot of fun.

36
00:02:30,985 --> 00:02:32,560
Ureshino-san.

37
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,550
Are you still working?

38
00:02:34,550 --> 00:02:39,740
Yeah. It's not a huge amount,
but I thought I'd try to finish it today.

39
00:02:39,740 --> 00:02:41,220
You're doing great work.

40
00:02:41,220 --> 00:02:43,300
Sorry, we'll be leaving first.

41
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:44,935
Have a good night.

42
00:02:44,935 --> 00:02:47,225
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

43
00:02:57,110 --> 00:03:00,880
♫ It's hard to resist the thing
that I've missed for so long ♫

44
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:02,710
♫ So long ♫

45
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:06,480
♫ Can't remember what it's like,
Just remember I need it ♫

46
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:08,990
♫ I need it ♫

47
00:03:08,990 --> 00:03:13,190
♫ You're not what I thought you were ♫

48
00:03:13,190 --> 00:03:15,120
♫ You were ♫

49
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:18,460
♫ To think I can't find a cure ♫

50
00:03:18,460 --> 00:03:21,070
♫ Find a cure ♫

51
00:03:21,070 --> 00:03:27,210
♫ Ooh, you're not what I thought ♫

52
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:37,320
[If Only You Weren't the One]

53
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:41,720
What a relief. We got in without a reservation.
[Episode 3]

54
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:45,050
Yeah, it's such a nice restaurant.

55
00:03:45,050 --> 00:03:46,900
Do you come here often?

56
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:49,400
No, it's my second time.

57
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,765
I always wanted to come here.

58
00:03:51,765 --> 00:03:57,800
So, before I invited you,
I came alone, just once.

59
00:03:57,800 --> 00:04:00,080
That's so sweet.

60
00:04:01,075 --> 00:04:02,750
I see.

61
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,605
I'm so happy. Thank you.

62
00:04:04,605 --> 00:04:08,265
Not at all. I should be the one thanking you.

63
00:04:13,975 --> 00:04:17,220
- Did I say something strange?
- Not at all.

64
00:04:17,220 --> 00:04:21,366
I'm just so grateful, I couldn't keep it in.

65
00:04:22,335 --> 00:04:24,698
What do you mean by that?

66
00:04:24,698 --> 00:04:26,600
Thank you for waiting. Your appetizer.

67
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:27,980
Wow!

68
00:04:27,980 --> 00:04:30,180
Wow, looks delicious.

69
00:04:30,180 --> 00:04:32,080
This is incredibly tasty.

70
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:34,140
- You had it once, right?
- Once.

71
00:04:34,140 --> 00:04:37,595
- Thank you. Let's eat.
- Let's eat.

72
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:46,030
During the meal, I was...

73
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:55,080
only thinking about Eisei Ureshino.

74
00:05:00,270 --> 00:05:02,750
I'll be at your place, Miporin.

75
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:20,420
Eisei's slender yet large hands.

76
00:05:31,630 --> 00:05:35,640
Those deep, dark eyes
that seem to pull you in...

77
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:46,000
His carefree smile and...

78
00:05:54,380 --> 00:05:56,290
It's a promise.

79
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:01,810
the words he said earlier.

80
00:06:08,695 --> 00:06:11,000
Sorry for making you pay.

81
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,690
It's fine. I invited you.

82
00:06:12,690 --> 00:06:14,475
But still...

83
00:06:14,475 --> 00:06:16,725
Then, next time.

84
00:06:16,725 --> 00:06:19,810
Next time, let's dine together again.

85
00:06:21,348 --> 00:06:22,670
Okay.

86
00:06:22,670 --> 00:06:24,118
Thank you.

87
00:06:24,118 --> 00:06:27,403
All right! It's a promise.

88
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,900
Ah.

89
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:35,040
It's raining tonight.

90
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:37,970
I didn't check the forecast at all.

91
00:06:37,970 --> 00:06:39,470
Please wait here for a moment.

92
00:06:39,470 --> 00:06:42,770
I'll buy an umbrella
at the convenience store.

93
00:06:42,770 --> 00:06:45,325
- I'll go too.
- It's fine.

94
00:06:45,325 --> 00:06:49,230
Please wait here, Onuma-san.

95
00:06:49,230 --> 00:06:51,820
- Thank you.
- I'll be right back.

96
00:07:08,875 --> 00:07:10,180
I'm back.

97
00:07:10,180 --> 00:07:12,595
They were sold out, huh?

98
00:07:12,595 --> 00:07:15,055
I can't take your umbrella.

99
00:07:16,260 --> 00:07:18,350
It was intentional.

100
00:07:19,335 --> 00:07:21,240
Intentional?

101
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:24,930
Oh, if it bothers you,
I'll go buy another.

102
00:07:29,210 --> 00:07:31,580
I don't mind.

103
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:35,590
Then, let's go.

104
00:07:35,590 --> 00:07:38,100
Okay. Let's go.

105
00:07:38,950 --> 00:07:41,740
- It's really pouring, isn't it?
- Right.

106
00:07:44,940 --> 00:07:46,720
Thank you.

107
00:07:57,365 --> 00:07:59,120
It's really pouring, isn't it?

108
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:01,215
Right.

109
00:08:01,215 --> 00:08:04,055
I didn't expect such a downpour.

110
00:08:04,855 --> 00:08:07,325
- Thank you.
- It's my pleasure.

111
00:08:07,325 --> 00:08:09,195
I'm glad.

112
00:08:17,375 --> 00:08:20,110
Kusaka-kun, you said you take the bus, right?

113
00:08:20,110 --> 00:08:21,835
I'm taking the train.

114
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:24,405
Oh, I'll walk you.

115
00:08:24,405 --> 00:08:25,650
Huh?

116
00:08:25,650 --> 00:08:29,870
Of course, I'll head home
after dropping you off.

117
00:08:29,870 --> 00:08:31,310
Thank you.

118
00:08:31,310 --> 00:08:34,480
But really, we can part ways here.

119
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:36,630
Are you sure?

120
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:38,152
Yeah.

121
00:08:38,152 --> 00:08:41,977
Okay, then. Please use this.

122
00:08:43,660 --> 00:08:45,630
Thank you.

123
00:08:52,836 --> 00:08:58,996
I'm sure the girl Kusaka-kun ends up dating...

124
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:04,140
will be happy.

125
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:20,280
[November 10, 10:07 p.m.]

126
00:09:22,795 --> 00:09:25,150
Then, let's meet after.

127
00:09:25,150 --> 00:09:26,600
What?

128
00:09:30,310 --> 00:09:32,860
I'll be at your place, Miporin.

129
00:10:17,070 --> 00:10:20,490
That was really fun today.

130
00:10:22,590 --> 00:10:25,370
The food was delicious too.

131
00:10:26,510 --> 00:10:30,470
Kusaka-kun is such a good guy.

132
00:10:30,470 --> 00:10:32,990
Really, a good guy.

133
00:10:33,685 --> 00:10:36,300
I wonder if he found an umbrella.

134
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:38,860
I hope he doesn't catch a cold.

135
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:43,990
He's not here. What a relief.

136
00:10:48,082 --> 00:10:56,482
[Thank you for today. It was fun.
Did you get home safely?]

137
00:10:59,940 --> 00:11:02,020
Coming.

138
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:07,750
Hey there!

139
00:11:08,860 --> 00:11:12,580
Work dragged on longer than I thought...

140
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:15,020
Huh?

141
00:11:15,020 --> 00:11:18,330
Hm? Miporin!

142
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:21,625
Miporin?

143
00:11:21,625 --> 00:11:23,690
Miporin!

144
00:11:23,690 --> 00:11:25,773
[Thank you for today.
I had a wonderful time.]

145
00:11:25,773 --> 00:11:27,788
[Did you get home safely?
I hope we can get dinner again!]

146
00:11:34,705 --> 00:11:36,630
Hey.

147
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:39,320
You're too loud.

148
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:41,050
Can I come in?

149
00:11:42,355 --> 00:11:43,570
Thanks for having me.

150
00:11:43,570 --> 00:11:48,230
I really hate this about him.

151
00:11:48,230 --> 00:11:51,610
He's so pushy. And self-centered.

152
00:11:51,610 --> 00:11:54,365
Don't yell so loudly outside my apartment.

153
00:11:54,365 --> 00:11:57,425
But you wouldn't open the door.

154
00:11:57,425 --> 00:12:01,980
Wow. I'm getting nostalgic.

155
00:12:02,995 --> 00:12:05,525
I've been thinking about moving for a while,

156
00:12:05,525 --> 00:12:08,990
but it's such a hassle, I keep putting it off.

157
00:12:08,990 --> 00:12:12,600
I know the feeling. My place is the same.

158
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,540
Hmm. Is that so?

159
00:12:14,540 --> 00:12:17,040
Well, I wouldn't know,
since I've never been there.

160
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:19,055
Oh, really?

161
00:12:19,055 --> 00:12:21,095
Come over next time.

162
00:12:22,220 --> 00:12:26,430
Wow, this bear brings back memories!

163
00:12:26,430 --> 00:12:30,050
This is that bear, right? Non-chan.

164
00:12:30,050 --> 00:12:33,860
The stuffed animal you treasured
since kindergarten, right?

165
00:12:33,860 --> 00:12:37,610
I'm impressed you remember that.

166
00:12:37,610 --> 00:12:39,370
Of course.

167
00:12:40,627 --> 00:12:42,910
I brought cake.

168
00:12:42,910 --> 00:12:44,210
Want some?

169
00:12:44,210 --> 00:12:48,195
Hey, haven't we been eating cake at night
too much lately?

170
00:12:48,195 --> 00:12:50,755
But it makes you happy, right?

171
00:12:52,306 --> 00:12:55,590
Alcohol is fine too.
I figured I'd pick some up.

172
00:12:55,590 --> 00:12:58,425
- Want one?
- Hmm...

173
00:12:58,425 --> 00:13:01,190
I'll pass.

174
00:13:01,190 --> 00:13:03,560
I'm full.

175
00:13:05,590 --> 00:13:07,940
Oh?

176
00:13:11,795 --> 00:13:16,200
What about you?
Did you eat something already?

177
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:19,230
Yeah.

178
00:13:21,296 --> 00:13:23,296
But whatever.

179
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:35,510
You're all wet.

180
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:42,970
You ran back
because you missed me, huh?

181
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:07,350
Hey.

182
00:14:09,470 --> 00:14:11,930
What did you two chat about?

183
00:14:21,410 --> 00:14:23,710
What did you do with him?

184
00:14:27,350 --> 00:14:30,110
Now, I get it.

185
00:14:30,110 --> 00:14:34,687
Why you always seem
to be having so much fun.

186
00:14:39,015 --> 00:14:41,090
This expression...

187
00:14:41,090 --> 00:14:43,990
I'm sure I have it too.

188
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:47,580
So...

189
00:15:07,690 --> 00:15:09,730
I won't tell you.

190
00:15:45,210 --> 00:15:49,780
After all, this feels so good...

191
00:16:20,650 --> 00:16:22,460
Morning.

192
00:16:24,030 --> 00:16:25,980
Good morning.

193
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:35,140
Last night, Miporin,
you were different from usual.

194
00:16:36,520 --> 00:16:38,080
What?

195
00:16:40,586 --> 00:16:42,866
It was really good.

196
00:16:44,230 --> 00:16:46,120
Stop it.

197
00:16:46,940 --> 00:16:51,000
I love how your character switches like that.

198
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:53,500
Stop it!

199
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:55,880
Why?

200
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:57,830
Look this way.

201
00:17:17,790 --> 00:17:24,620
If we were dating, would it be like this?

202
00:18:13,460 --> 00:18:15,620
What about breakfast?

203
00:18:15,620 --> 00:18:18,955
I can make some rice balls or miso soup.

204
00:18:18,955 --> 00:18:21,170
Oh...

205
00:18:21,170 --> 00:18:23,520
Nah, I'm more of a bread guy.

206
00:18:24,820 --> 00:18:28,910
Oh, I didn't know that.

207
00:18:28,910 --> 00:18:31,826
I can't help but laugh at myself.

208
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:37,315
I don't know anything
about this man, and yet...

209
00:18:37,315 --> 00:18:39,310
Can I use your bathroom?

210
00:18:39,310 --> 00:18:41,050
Oh, sure.

211
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:49,550
If we were dating, huh?

212
00:18:52,835 --> 00:18:56,460
Hey, could you walk a little farther away?

213
00:18:56,460 --> 00:18:58,300
Miporin, you changed clothes today, so it's fine.

214
00:18:58,300 --> 00:19:01,410
It's not about that. I just don't like it.

215
00:19:01,410 --> 00:19:02,950
You don't?

216
00:19:02,950 --> 00:19:05,160
What? Did you start hating me?

217
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:09,965
Wow, we were so close until this morning!

218
00:19:09,965 --> 00:19:12,765
You're going to make me really hate you.

219
00:19:12,765 --> 00:19:14,470
So scary.

220
00:19:15,185 --> 00:19:18,940
What I mean is, I hate acting
as if nothing happened,

221
00:19:18,940 --> 00:19:21,765
putting on this phony face.

222
00:19:23,925 --> 00:19:26,270
Oh, that's all that bothered you?

223
00:19:26,270 --> 00:19:28,770
"That's all"?

224
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:36,940
What?

225
00:19:38,635 --> 00:19:40,757
We're alone now.

226
00:19:40,757 --> 00:19:42,417
Stop it.

227
00:19:42,417 --> 00:19:44,167
Stop what?

228
00:19:48,807 --> 00:19:51,797
Oh, good morning.

229
00:19:51,797 --> 00:19:54,705
- Morning.
- Good morning.

230
00:19:54,705 --> 00:19:57,270
Looks like you had fun yesterday.

231
00:19:58,045 --> 00:19:59,200
Huh?

232
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:03,040
Onuma-san was gushing about it.

233
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:06,550
Oh, but she wouldn't tell me the details.

234
00:20:09,695 --> 00:20:12,250
Were you okay yesterday, with the rain?

235
00:20:12,250 --> 00:20:15,510
Sorry, I fell asleep
and saw your text this morning.

236
00:20:15,510 --> 00:20:17,280
It's totally fine.

237
00:20:17,280 --> 00:20:19,830
Did you get home safely too?

238
00:20:19,830 --> 00:20:21,930
Yes. Thanks to you.

239
00:20:21,930 --> 00:20:23,320
That's good then.

240
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:27,481
Let's go together again
if I find another delicious restaurant.

241
00:20:27,481 --> 00:20:29,245
Okay.

242
00:20:29,245 --> 00:20:31,130
So direct, huh?

243
00:20:31,130 --> 00:20:33,120
Not at all.

244
00:20:33,120 --> 00:20:35,810
You two know each other
from college, right?

245
00:20:35,810 --> 00:20:37,420
That's right.

246
00:20:37,420 --> 00:20:40,440
So, if you're curious about her,
ask me anything.

247
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:41,730
Hey!

248
00:20:41,730 --> 00:20:44,005
Oh, can I?

249
00:20:44,005 --> 00:20:46,266
Of course.

250
00:20:46,266 --> 00:20:48,476
Right?

251
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:53,160
You don't know anything about me.

252
00:20:55,889 --> 00:20:59,330
Well, I have to go prepare
for my presentation, so excuse me.

253
00:20:59,330 --> 00:21:06,400
♫ Hold me close, stay by my side ♫

254
00:21:07,775 --> 00:21:10,037
He's so obvious.

255
00:21:10,037 --> 00:21:14,506
Shut up. Stop saying weird things.

256
00:21:15,450 --> 00:21:17,360
Who is?

257
00:21:20,070 --> 00:21:23,250
♫ We wouldn't... ♫

258
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:27,790
Come on, are you gushing or conflicted?
Which is it?

259
00:21:27,790 --> 00:21:31,859
I'm conflicted. I'm not gushing
even a micrometer.

260
00:21:31,859 --> 00:21:36,215
Then, there's only one answer.
Kusaka-boy's the one.

261
00:21:36,215 --> 00:21:38,580
Well, yeah, that's true.

262
00:21:38,580 --> 00:21:46,300
I know, but that's exactly
why I'm conflicted, right?

263
00:21:46,300 --> 00:21:49,490
Huh? I don't get it.

264
00:21:49,490 --> 00:21:51,312
You're gushing, aren't you?

265
00:21:51,312 --> 00:21:55,532
I'm sacrificing
my precious lunch break for this.

266
00:21:56,580 --> 00:21:58,886
I'm sorry.

267
00:21:58,886 --> 00:22:03,530
I'll treat you to those donuts
you wanted next time.

268
00:22:03,530 --> 00:22:07,880
It's a promise. You have to wait
at least an hour for those.

269
00:22:07,880 --> 00:22:09,350
Yes.

270
00:22:10,575 --> 00:22:14,175
Well, to answer seriously,
it's up to you, Mihono.

271
00:22:14,175 --> 00:22:16,265
I've told you this.

272
00:22:17,770 --> 00:22:22,430
No one can decide this for you.
It's your choice.

273
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:26,860
Yeah, you're right.

274
00:22:30,025 --> 00:22:33,310
Oh, Mihono-san, there you are!

275
00:22:33,310 --> 00:22:35,089
Yuri-chan, what is it?

276
00:22:35,089 --> 00:22:39,310
Mihono-san, I have a huge favor to ask!

277
00:22:47,985 --> 00:22:50,100
What is this?

278
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:52,070
- Ureshino-san.
- Here.

279
00:22:52,070 --> 00:22:54,020
- Kusaka-san.
- Here.

280
00:22:54,020 --> 00:22:56,210
- Onuma-san.
- Here.

281
00:22:56,210 --> 00:22:58,545
- Everyone's here.
- Thank you.

282
00:22:59,715 --> 00:23:01,330
We'll be departing shortly.

283
00:23:01,330 --> 00:23:03,710
Enjoy the journey to Rinkai Hot Springs!

284
00:23:03,710 --> 00:23:07,530
Yeah!

285
00:23:08,660 --> 00:23:12,160
How did things turn out like this?

286
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,875
[Preview]

287
00:23:13,875 --> 00:23:18,460
- Look.
- I had wanted to eat those strawberries.

288
00:23:18,460 --> 00:23:20,905
I'm really getting sick of this.

289
00:23:20,905 --> 00:23:24,345
I just wanted to do
something like this with you.

290
00:23:25,345 --> 00:23:27,150
I won't hold back.

291
00:23:27,150 --> 00:23:30,280
If only I could be true to these feelings,

292
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:32,250
things would be so much easier.

293
00:23:32,250 --> 00:23:35,020
Why do you think I call you "Miporin"?

294
00:23:35,020 --> 00:23:37,980
What is it that has such a hold over me?

295
00:23:37,980 --> 00:23:39,480
The thrill?

296
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:41,765
The possessiveness?
[This drama is fiction.]

297
00:23:41,765 --> 00:23:43,505
Or love?
[This drama is fiction.]
